WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:04.858 --> 00:00:06.481
- CLAIRE: <i>Previously</i>...
- Where is the gold?

2
00:00:06.538 --> 00:00:09.492
The Silkie
from the sea.

3
00:00:10.226 --> 00:00:12.160
Are you sure the patrol
caught sight of him here?

4
00:00:12.218 --> 00:00:13.238
Yes. sir.

5
00:00:13.248 --> 00:00:15.405
Thought they saw him
swimming out to the islands.

6
00:00:15.541 --> 00:00:16.881
CLAIRE:
Did you ever fall in love

7
00:00:17.001 --> 00:00:18.770
with anyone else after I left?

8
00:00:18.936 --> 00:00:21.803
No. Sassenach.
I never loved anyone but you.

9
00:00:22.030 --> 00:00:23.319
So good to see you.

10
00:00:23.416 --> 00:00:26.248
IAN: Jenny and I.
we grieved of you for years.

11
00:00:26.358 --> 00:00:28.573
It's Young Ian.
He's run off again.

12
00:00:28.673 --> 00:00:29.793
IAN: Have you seen him?
- No.

13
00:00:29.874 --> 00:00:31.676
CLAIRE: Since when do you lie
to your family?

14
00:00:31.776 --> 00:00:32.928
JAMIE: I'm the only one
teaching him

15
00:00:32.985 --> 00:00:34.959
- the ways of the world.
- Who the hell are you?

16
00:00:35.501 --> 00:00:36.835
Ah!

17
00:00:36.928 --> 00:00:39.092
Your uncle's been a busy man.

18
00:00:39.170 --> 00:00:40.689
But inciting sedition?

19
00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:42.021
Leave! Now!

20
00:00:45.470 --> 00:00:46.637
Please bring Young Ian home.

21
00:00:46.824 --> 00:00:49.327
I'll take the lad home
to Lallybroch.

22
00:00:51.611 --> 00:00:54.080
WOMAN: ♪ Sing me a song ♪

23
00:00:54.165 --> 00:00:57.168
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

24
00:00:57.268 --> 00:00:59.904
♪ Say. could that lass ♪

25
00:00:59.970 --> 00:01:02.082
♪ Be I? ♪

26
00:01:02.691 --> 00:01:04.753
♪ Merry of soul ♪

27
00:01:04.811 --> 00:01:07.941
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

28
00:01:08.011 --> 00:01:10.147
♪ Over the sea ♪

29
00:01:10.247 --> 00:01:13.050
♪ To Skye ♪

30
00:01:13.332 --> 00:01:15.453
♪ Billow and breeze ♪

31
00:01:15.553 --> 00:01:18.363
♪ Islands and seas ♪

32
00:01:18.472 --> 00:01:23.428
♪ Mountains of rain and sun ♪

33
00:01:23.582 --> 00:01:26.082
♪ All that was good ♪

34
00:01:26.207 --> 00:01:28.769
♪ All that was fair ♪

35
00:01:28.863 --> 00:01:30.871
♪ All that was me ♪

36
00:01:30.972 --> 00:01:34.105
♪ Is gone ♪

37
00:01:34.205 --> 00:01:36.107
♪ Sing me a song ♪

38
00:01:36.207 --> 00:01:39.477
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

39
00:01:39.577 --> 00:01:41.713
♪ Say. could that lass ♪

40
00:01:41.813 --> 00:01:44.384
♪ Be I? ♪

41
00:01:44.496 --> 00:01:46.131
♪ Merry of soul ♪

42
00:01:46.317 --> 00:01:49.681
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

43
00:01:49.791 --> 00:01:53.395
♪ Over the sea ♪

44
00:01:53.573 --> 00:01:58.711
♪ To Skye ♪

45
00:01:59.821 --> 00:02:04.069
♪♪
<font color=#FF00FF>*OUTLANDER*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 03  Episode 08</font>

46
00:02:06.034 --> 00:02:08.601
♪♪
Episode Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"First Wife"</font>

47
00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:16.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

48
00:02:23.354 --> 00:02:26.190
♪♪ Pensive music...

49
00:02:26.290 --> 00:02:29.760
♪♪

50
00:02:35.322 --> 00:02:37.034
CLAIRE: Here I was.

51
00:02:37.502 --> 00:02:39.705
at the place
that had been imprinted forever

52
00:02:39.791 --> 00:02:42.400
in my head and on my heart.

53
00:02:42.852 --> 00:02:44.916
It was home once.

54
00:02:45.318 --> 00:02:48.330
It didn't appear
that anything had changed.

55
00:02:48.550 --> 00:02:52.166
but somehow.
nothing felt the same.

56
00:02:55.653 --> 00:02:56.888
[ clicks tongue ]

57
00:03:10.607 --> 00:03:13.476
Never thought I'd see ye
grace my front step again.

58
00:03:17.903 --> 00:03:19.539
Me neither.

59
00:03:20.193 --> 00:03:21.526
When Ian said
ye were still alive.

60
00:03:21.584 --> 00:03:24.482
ye might have knocked me down
with a feather.

61
00:03:25.084 --> 00:03:28.404
I-I know it...
It must be quite a shock.

62
00:03:32.412 --> 00:03:34.678
But here I am.

63
00:03:35.235 --> 00:03:37.037
Here ye are.

64
00:03:40.233 --> 00:03:42.076
Well. you look well.

65
00:03:44.704 --> 00:03:46.521
How are the children?

66
00:03:46.715 --> 00:03:47.842
Grown now.

67
00:03:47.982 --> 00:03:50.521
Some wi' bairns of their own.

68
00:03:53.394 --> 00:03:55.693
Ye had me worried half to death.

69
00:03:58.053 --> 00:03:59.294
I dinna mean
to worry ye. but...

70
00:03:59.383 --> 00:04:00.785
IAN: Better get inside. lad.

71
00:04:00.843 --> 00:04:03.084
before your tongue gets ye
in more trouble.

72
00:04:04.989 --> 00:04:08.639
♪♪

73
00:04:26.571 --> 00:04:29.111
IAN: Jamie. why did ye not just
tell me he was wi' you?

74
00:04:29.233 --> 00:04:30.901
Your sister was worried sick!

75
00:04:30.966 --> 00:04:32.748
YOUNG IAN: Because if he had.
ye'd have brought me back home.

76
00:04:32.805 --> 00:04:34.853
JENNY: Aye. he'd have
brought ye home where ye belong.

77
00:04:34.910 --> 00:04:37.943
Feeding chickens. when I could
be in the city earning a wage?

78
00:04:38.001 --> 00:04:39.305
So that's what ye were doing?

79
00:04:39.392 --> 00:04:40.563
Earning a wage. eh?

80
00:04:40.621 --> 00:04:42.953
Aye. and I was good at it too!

81
00:04:43.252 --> 00:04:44.320
Fergus said so.

82
00:04:44.428 --> 00:04:45.697
Said I was a natural.

83
00:04:45.797 --> 00:04:47.778
I sold 20 cask of brandy

84
00:04:47.842 --> 00:04:49.551
before we were forced to flee
after the fire.

85
00:04:49.608 --> 00:04:51.805
What fire?
And why did you have to flee?

86
00:04:51.863 --> 00:04:54.914
You had my son sellin' liquor
and consortin' with criminals?

87
00:04:56.680 --> 00:04:58.747
[ sighs ]
I told you I would look out

88
00:04:58.805 --> 00:05:00.235
for the boy. and I did.

89
00:05:00.352 --> 00:05:02.847
Then there was a wee fire
at the print shop.

90
00:05:02.947 --> 00:05:03.948
IAN: Wee?

91
00:05:04.048 --> 00:05:06.727
Ye wouldna be standing here
if it was wee.

92
00:05:08.244 --> 00:05:09.846
There's nothing left then?

93
00:05:12.830 --> 00:05:15.117
So that's why ye're home.
tail dragging.

94
00:05:15.259 --> 00:05:16.836
And wi' a stray.

95
00:05:17.228 --> 00:05:19.735
Who's drop back into our lives
after 20 years

96
00:05:19.813 --> 00:05:21.867
as though nothing's changed.

97
00:05:23.493 --> 00:05:26.463
Everything was fine
in Edinburgh. Janet.

98
00:05:26.766 --> 00:05:29.234
Then an agent of the Crown
started extorting me.

99
00:05:29.466 --> 00:05:31.164
Sent his ruffian after Claire.

100
00:05:31.360 --> 00:05:34.345
Auntie Claire killed him.
Killed him good.

101
00:05:36.848 --> 00:05:39.884
♪♪ Suspenseful music...

102
00:05:39.984 --> 00:05:42.000
♪♪♪

103
00:05:42.084 --> 00:05:43.853
Outside. Now.

104
00:05:45.620 --> 00:05:46.672
[ sighs ]

105
00:05:46.967 --> 00:05:48.836
And you better be
where I can find you

106
00:05:48.894 --> 00:05:51.096
when it's time
for your thrashin'.

107
00:05:51.228 --> 00:05:54.610
♪♪

108
00:05:56.067 --> 00:05:57.852
You killed a man
in front of my boy?

109
00:05:57.910 --> 00:06:00.046
He wasn't there
when it happened.

110
00:06:00.169 --> 00:06:01.704
I had no choice.

111
00:06:01.993 --> 00:06:03.708
Th-the man attacked me.

112
00:06:03.915 --> 00:06:06.157
CLAIRE: I was defending myself.

113
00:06:06.258 --> 00:06:07.927
But there's more to it
than just...

114
00:06:07.985 --> 00:06:08.988
JENNY: Oh. well. then.

115
00:06:09.046 --> 00:06:10.735
mebbe we should all gather
around the fire.

116
00:06:10.808 --> 00:06:12.552
I mean. if we're to listen
to a tall tale.

117
00:06:12.610 --> 00:06:15.133
Ye do not complain when I
send you money every month.

118
00:06:15.196 --> 00:06:16.766
and you know fine well
it doesn't come

119
00:06:16.824 --> 00:06:18.208
from printing copies
o' the Psalms.

120
00:06:18.266 --> 00:06:19.997
JENNY: Aye. I ken
how you make your money.

121
00:06:20.055 --> 00:06:21.292
but that's you. brother.

122
00:06:21.392 --> 00:06:23.427
You could have taught young Ian
the printing trade.

123
00:06:23.534 --> 00:06:25.052
not how to be a criminal.

124
00:06:25.110 --> 00:06:26.139
JAMIE: I promise ye.

125
00:06:26.197 --> 00:06:28.040
I treated him
as if he was my own son.

126
00:06:28.116 --> 00:06:29.235
IAN: Aye.

127
00:06:31.671 --> 00:06:34.437
Then ye can punish him
as yer own.

128
00:06:34.709 --> 00:06:37.648
♪♪

129
00:06:37.811 --> 00:06:41.749
Mebbe there's another way
he can make it up to ye.

130
00:06:43.614 --> 00:06:45.983
Och.
I hate this.

131
00:06:46.132 --> 00:06:47.730
Stinks like the devil's arse.

132
00:06:47.788 --> 00:06:49.109
If Ma hears yer cursin'...

133
00:06:49.179 --> 00:06:51.742
No one likes
a wee clype. Janet.

134
00:06:54.550 --> 00:06:56.148
You're getting covered
with muck.

135
00:06:56.206 --> 00:06:58.539
Well. you're covered
with foxtails. so there.

136
00:06:59.725 --> 00:07:00.887
'Tis no fair.

137
00:07:00.965 --> 00:07:02.992
Ye run away.
and ye don't even get yer thrashin'.

138
00:07:03.050 --> 00:07:04.351
This is a boy's task.

139
00:07:04.441 --> 00:07:06.043
Matthew should be doing this.

140
00:07:06.111 --> 00:07:07.984
I'd rather get a thrashin'.

141
00:07:10.708 --> 00:07:12.711
You've even got muck
'round yer mouth.

142
00:07:12.769 --> 00:07:14.705
Oh. it isna muck.
It's whiskers.

143
00:07:14.929 --> 00:07:16.280
Whiskers?
You?

144
00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:17.915
- Aye.
- Ha!

145
00:07:24.161 --> 00:07:26.063
Ye may have been right.

146
00:07:28.625 --> 00:07:30.864
As were you.

147
00:07:31.270 --> 00:07:32.739
I shoulda sent word.

148
00:07:32.964 --> 00:07:34.638
told ye he was with me.

149
00:07:34.888 --> 00:07:36.747
and I didn't.

150
00:07:37.287 --> 00:07:38.958
I'm sorry.

151
00:07:40.817 --> 00:07:43.486
It's only that the lad
loves ye so. Jamie.

152
00:07:43.595 --> 00:07:45.302
IAN: He follows ye around
like a pup.

153
00:07:45.509 --> 00:07:47.583
hanging on yer every word.

154
00:07:47.945 --> 00:07:51.015
[ ♪♪ Pensive music ]

155
00:07:51.115 --> 00:07:53.585
♪♪

156
00:07:53.877 --> 00:07:55.358
GIRL: Henry!

157
00:07:55.519 --> 00:07:56.835
♪

158
00:07:56.911 --> 00:07:58.345
Hey!

159
00:07:58.555 --> 00:08:00.157
Give it back!

160
00:08:00.257 --> 00:08:01.625
Henry!

161
00:08:01.725 --> 00:08:03.594
JENNY: Och! Ye wee devils!

162
00:08:03.694 --> 00:08:06.230
That'll be your supper then.

163
00:08:07.347 --> 00:08:09.249
You certainly have
a full house.

164
00:08:09.498 --> 00:08:10.590
Hello.

165
00:08:10.754 --> 00:08:12.387
I'm Claire.

166
00:08:12.774 --> 00:08:14.943
This is Angus and Anthony.

167
00:08:15.239 --> 00:08:16.874
Oh. it's a pleasure
to meet both of you

168
00:08:16.932 --> 00:08:18.645
fine young gentlemen.

169
00:08:18.845 --> 00:08:20.146
Go on.

170
00:08:23.103 --> 00:08:24.772
They're Maggie's.

171
00:08:24.928 --> 00:08:28.264
Ye remember holding Maggie
in this very room?

172
00:08:28.856 --> 00:08:30.777
Of course.

173
00:08:31.066 --> 00:08:34.215
You were so certain
she was going to be a boy.

174
00:08:37.246 --> 00:08:38.931
Strange to think
she's old enough

175
00:08:39.063 --> 00:08:40.464
to have children
of her own now.

176
00:08:40.564 --> 00:08:44.135
Eh. well. that's what happens
when 20 years go by.

177
00:08:45.235 --> 00:08:47.104
I heard we had visitors.

178
00:08:50.007 --> 00:08:51.242
I'm James Murray.

179
00:08:51.342 --> 00:08:52.509
[ baby babbles ]

180
00:08:52.609 --> 00:08:54.378
[ chuckles ]
Wee Jamie.

181
00:08:54.478 --> 00:08:57.281
Well. you're certainly
not so "wee" anymore.

182
00:08:58.737 --> 00:09:01.727
The last time I saw you.
you were barely tall enough

183
00:09:01.785 --> 00:09:04.262
to see over the top
of a washtub.

184
00:09:04.802 --> 00:09:06.337
Claire used to live
in Lallybroch

185
00:09:06.407 --> 00:09:08.027
when you were
about Matthew's age.

186
00:09:08.183 --> 00:09:10.338
Our Jamie here
is now husband to Joan

187
00:09:10.396 --> 00:09:15.068
and father to Henry. Matthew.
Caroline. and new wee Benjamin.

188
00:09:16.065 --> 00:09:17.418
[ baby fusses ]

189
00:09:17.476 --> 00:09:19.411
I'll away out
and see my uncle then.

190
00:09:19.803 --> 00:09:22.306
[ baby crying ]

191
00:09:22.574 --> 00:09:24.277
Och. he's wet himself.

192
00:09:24.487 --> 00:09:26.189
Can I help?

193
00:09:26.375 --> 00:09:29.779
Dinna want to bewilder the bairn
wi' a strange face. now.

194
00:09:29.996 --> 00:09:33.099
[ baby crying ]

195
00:09:41.445 --> 00:09:46.417
Young Ian's made enough dall
for a month's supply of fuel.

196
00:09:46.697 --> 00:09:48.299
The lad's paying for his crimes.

197
00:09:48.399 --> 00:09:50.921
Our father woulda had ye
over the gate.

198
00:09:51.518 --> 00:09:55.222
Aye. but a thrashing's not
the only way to teach a lesson.

199
00:09:55.280 --> 00:09:58.450
Ye're an authority
on raising bairns now?

200
00:10:00.119 --> 00:10:01.609
No.

201
00:10:05.238 --> 00:10:08.929
No. but I am
an authority

202
00:10:08.987 --> 00:10:12.804
on being a 16-year-old lad
that lives on a farm.

203
00:10:13.437 --> 00:10:15.515
Ye treat him as a child.
but he's a man now.

204
00:10:15.573 --> 00:10:16.742
[ scoffs ]

205
00:10:16.864 --> 00:10:18.937
Ye ought to give him
a taste of freedom.

206
00:10:19.077 --> 00:10:20.607
while he still thinks
it's yours to give.

207
00:10:20.664 --> 00:10:22.023
[ inhales deeply ]

208
00:10:22.126 --> 00:10:25.476
Listen to you.
telling me what I should do.

209
00:10:25.756 --> 00:10:28.132
Ye must ken it's a mortal sin
to take another wife

210
00:10:28.190 --> 00:10:30.058
while the first
still walks the earth.

211
00:10:32.937 --> 00:10:34.375
I would never have taken a bride

212
00:10:34.433 --> 00:10:36.202
if I thought
Claire was still alive.

213
00:10:36.420 --> 00:10:38.527
Since ye believed her
to be dead.

214
00:10:38.585 --> 00:10:41.118
why didn't ye share
yer grief wi' me?

215
00:10:45.858 --> 00:10:48.617
I barely wanted to breathe.
let alone speak of it.

216
00:10:53.378 --> 00:10:55.147
I ken.

217
00:10:56.179 --> 00:10:57.521
But ye must speak of it now.

218
00:10:57.579 --> 00:10:59.348
I need to know what happened.

219
00:11:00.646 --> 00:11:03.482
♪♪ Soft tense music...

220
00:11:03.540 --> 00:11:06.460
♪

221
00:11:06.648 --> 00:11:10.312
I was prepared to die
on the battlefield at Culloden.

222
00:11:11.030 --> 00:11:12.998
With me dead.

223
00:11:13.254 --> 00:11:16.958
it would've been dangerous
for Claire to stay. so...

224
00:11:20.892 --> 00:11:25.375
So I arranged for her
to hide at an inn.

225
00:11:25.705 --> 00:11:28.765
Gave her money
for safe passage to the Colonies

226
00:11:29.078 --> 00:11:32.085
after things had settled down.

227
00:11:32.810 --> 00:11:36.214
Later. I heard the British
went through the village.

228
00:11:36.307 --> 00:11:40.132
killing everyone...
Man. woman. and child.

229
00:11:40.710 --> 00:11:42.245
But she got away?

230
00:11:42.369 --> 00:11:44.571
♪

231
00:11:44.687 --> 00:11:46.312
Aye.

232
00:11:46.731 --> 00:11:49.117
She thought I'd died in battle.

233
00:11:49.212 --> 00:11:53.890
So she boarded a ship
to the Colonies.

234
00:11:54.445 --> 00:11:56.539
I didna ken it at the time.

235
00:11:57.210 --> 00:11:58.460
I sat on these very steps

236
00:11:58.529 --> 00:12:00.109
watchin' this very road
with Claire

237
00:12:00.167 --> 00:12:02.136
when you were taken
by the redcoats.

238
00:12:02.224 --> 00:12:03.491
When you didna come home.

239
00:12:03.549 --> 00:12:05.385
we rode together to find you.

240
00:12:05.550 --> 00:12:09.070
The Claire I kent would never
have stopped looking for you.

241
00:12:09.406 --> 00:12:13.015
♪♪

242
00:12:20.874 --> 00:12:22.375
JAMIE:
We could build a cottage.

243
00:12:22.719 --> 00:12:25.109
on the western edge of the land.

244
00:12:25.472 --> 00:12:28.437
We could make
a life here. Claire.

245
00:12:29.389 --> 00:12:32.664
Except that Jenny can barely
stand the sight of me.

246
00:12:34.051 --> 00:12:35.352
Yet. perhaps...

247
00:12:35.859 --> 00:12:37.453
perhaps we should
tell her the truth.

248
00:12:37.511 --> 00:12:39.546
[ scoffs ]
We say ye traveled

249
00:12:39.604 --> 00:12:41.343
from another time.
ye may as well convince her

250
00:12:41.400 --> 00:12:42.467
ye're a mermaid.

251
00:12:44.046 --> 00:12:45.703
Murtagh understood.

252
00:12:45.761 --> 00:12:47.976
That was a chance
we had to take

253
00:12:48.132 --> 00:12:51.539
wi' a... a man
that's been out in the world.

254
00:12:51.918 --> 00:12:55.429
Jenny has never left this farm.

255
00:12:55.829 --> 00:12:59.632
We're always at loggerheads.

256
00:12:59.795 --> 00:13:02.640
She'll be full of questions
we have no answers for.

257
00:13:10.193 --> 00:13:12.362
But if I don't tell her
the truth. then...

258
00:13:12.587 --> 00:13:15.773
there will always be
this wall between us.

259
00:13:16.274 --> 00:13:20.179
Jenny casts a very warm light
on those that she trusts

260
00:13:20.369 --> 00:13:23.172
and a very cold shadow
on those that she doesn't.

261
00:13:25.753 --> 00:13:27.222
Aye.

262
00:13:33.577 --> 00:13:35.640
Sometimes...

263
00:13:37.711 --> 00:13:40.113
I still canna believe
ye're truly here.

264
00:13:45.225 --> 00:13:49.129
I went searching for ye...

265
00:13:49.284 --> 00:13:51.486
once.

266
00:13:51.781 --> 00:13:54.351
The day I escaped Ardsmuir.

267
00:13:54.784 --> 00:13:56.320
You escaped?

268
00:13:56.653 --> 00:13:57.988
Aye.

269
00:14:00.977 --> 00:14:03.898
There was a man
named Duncan Kerr.

270
00:14:04.276 --> 00:14:07.390
Claimed there was treasure
hidden on an island.

271
00:14:07.703 --> 00:14:09.226
He was fevered.

272
00:14:09.431 --> 00:14:11.133
Kent he was dying.

273
00:14:12.436 --> 00:14:15.505
It was his only chance
to tell someone

274
00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:17.460
he thought he could trust.

275
00:14:18.902 --> 00:14:20.867
His last words
were that the treasure

276
00:14:20.992 --> 00:14:22.789
was guarded

277
00:14:23.151 --> 00:14:25.654
by a buidseach bàn.

278
00:14:25.919 --> 00:14:28.088
La dame blanche.

279
00:14:29.958 --> 00:14:32.260
A white witch.

280
00:14:33.068 --> 00:14:34.704
My heart...

281
00:14:37.341 --> 00:14:40.789
Almost stopped
when he said it.

282
00:14:40.847 --> 00:14:42.215
I...

283
00:14:42.392 --> 00:14:46.742
I thought maybe you'd returned.

284
00:14:47.562 --> 00:14:50.390
that you were out there.

285
00:14:50.449 --> 00:14:52.210
♪♪

286
00:14:52.328 --> 00:14:55.906
JAMIE: There are hundreds
of isles all down the coast.

287
00:14:56.401 --> 00:14:59.125
but only one
where the selchs live.

288
00:14:59.804 --> 00:15:02.573
Silkie Island.

289
00:15:02.752 --> 00:15:05.589
♪♪ Dramatic music...

290
00:15:05.689 --> 00:15:08.343
♪♪

291
00:15:08.514 --> 00:15:10.804
I swam to it.

292
00:15:11.252 --> 00:15:13.087
Out of my mind with cold.

293
00:15:13.578 --> 00:15:16.548
♪♪

294
00:15:19.536 --> 00:15:22.406
[ panting ]

295
00:15:22.662 --> 00:15:25.631
♪♪

296
00:15:41.591 --> 00:15:44.826
♪♪

297
00:15:50.567 --> 00:15:51.768
[ grunts ]

298
00:15:51.883 --> 00:15:53.685
Claire.

299
00:15:55.602 --> 00:15:58.339
Claire! Claire!

300
00:16:00.306 --> 00:16:02.708
♪♪

301
00:16:02.801 --> 00:16:05.704
Of course.
I didn't find you there.

302
00:16:05.882 --> 00:16:08.429
♪♪

303
00:16:08.744 --> 00:16:12.155
I realized it was foolish
to think you'd come back.

304
00:16:14.287 --> 00:16:16.589
If he hadna been dead already.
I...

305
00:16:18.662 --> 00:16:21.835
I woulda gone back
and killed Kerr myself.

306
00:16:23.033 --> 00:16:25.002
For giving me hope.

307
00:16:26.226 --> 00:16:27.272
[ grunts softly ]

308
00:16:27.561 --> 00:16:29.606
♪

309
00:16:30.015 --> 00:16:31.941
And then I noticed it.

310
00:16:32.483 --> 00:16:34.366
The MacKenzie crest.

311
00:16:34.522 --> 00:16:36.680
♪

312
00:16:36.780 --> 00:16:38.848
Etched into stone.

313
00:16:39.116 --> 00:16:41.757
just like Kerr had told me.

314
00:16:42.147 --> 00:16:45.021
That's where I found
the treasure.

315
00:16:47.624 --> 00:16:51.241
At least Kerr had been right
about that.

316
00:16:51.467 --> 00:16:54.445
♪♪

317
00:16:54.944 --> 00:16:59.756
The box was full
of ancient coins and gems...

318
00:17:00.100 --> 00:17:02.733
Rubies. emeralds.

319
00:17:02.897 --> 00:17:06.053
three large sapphires.

320
00:17:06.459 --> 00:17:11.920
I took one and gave it
to the governor of the prison.

321
00:17:13.694 --> 00:17:15.185
You were free.

322
00:17:15.741 --> 00:17:18.222
You had the treasure.

323
00:17:18.787 --> 00:17:21.125
Why did you go back
to the prison?

324
00:17:21.678 --> 00:17:24.092
Couldna take it with me.

325
00:17:24.686 --> 00:17:27.197
Besides. the prisoners
needed me.

326
00:17:27.936 --> 00:17:29.166
I was their leader.

327
00:17:36.685 --> 00:17:38.820
I wasn't on an island.

328
00:17:41.202 --> 00:17:43.319
But I was out there.

329
00:17:44.155 --> 00:17:46.750
Wishing you'd come and find me.

330
00:17:48.709 --> 00:17:50.483
Sounds silly. but...

331
00:17:51.006 --> 00:17:54.624
whenever I would hear
birdsong...

332
00:17:55.225 --> 00:17:58.108
I would pretend
it was you talking to me.

333
00:17:58.623 --> 00:18:00.230
Hmm.

334
00:18:02.569 --> 00:18:05.577
Ye ken the...
greylag.

335
00:18:05.787 --> 00:18:07.904
yeah. it mates for life?

336
00:18:08.334 --> 00:18:10.530
You kill a grown one.

337
00:18:10.764 --> 00:18:14.233
out hunting.
you must wait...

338
00:18:16.342 --> 00:18:19.383
For its mate will come to mourn.

339
00:18:21.537 --> 00:18:24.412
Then ye must kill that one too.

340
00:18:25.014 --> 00:18:28.959
otherwise. it will
grieve itself to death...

341
00:18:30.600 --> 00:18:34.561
Calling through the skies
for the lost one.

342
00:18:34.764 --> 00:18:38.459
♪♪

343
00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:01.842
What is it?

344
00:19:04.880 --> 00:19:05.981
Jamie?

345
00:19:06.039 --> 00:19:08.681
Something I've been meaning
to tell ye. Sassenach.

346
00:19:08.898 --> 00:19:11.533
Hasna been easy
keeping it from ye.

347
00:19:12.376 --> 00:19:14.416
I was hoping to speak
to Ned Gowan before I told ye.

348
00:19:14.689 --> 00:19:18.041
[ inhales ] to see if the law
was in our favor.

349
00:19:18.141 --> 00:19:20.331
Ned Gowan is still alive?

350
00:19:20.601 --> 00:19:22.236
It's very complicated.

351
00:19:23.917 --> 00:19:26.636
Ye must listen
wi' all yer heart.

352
00:19:26.747 --> 00:19:28.148
[ door creaks open ]

353
00:19:28.206 --> 00:19:29.527
JOAN: Daddy.

354
00:19:30.097 --> 00:19:31.972
Daddy. who is that woman?

355
00:19:32.167 --> 00:19:33.078
Daddy?

356
00:19:33.136 --> 00:19:34.136
[ footsteps approaching ]

357
00:19:34.224 --> 00:19:36.893
[ suspenseful music ]

358
00:19:37.245 --> 00:19:38.386
Sassenach witch!

359
00:19:38.444 --> 00:19:40.386
JAMIE: Laoghaire. what the...

360
00:19:40.705 --> 00:19:43.042
Laoghaire. what the hell
are you doing here?

361
00:19:43.175 --> 00:19:46.261
Ye're... ye're supposed
to be dead!

362
00:19:47.972 --> 00:19:49.339
How?

363
00:19:49.784 --> 00:19:52.261
How could ye do such a thing
to me. Jamie Fraser?

364
00:19:52.441 --> 00:19:54.027
Slip home behind my back?

365
00:19:54.097 --> 00:19:55.516
Put yer prick in that whore?

366
00:19:55.574 --> 00:19:57.353
- Ma. please. We shouldna be here.
- JAMIE: Be still.

367
00:19:57.410 --> 00:19:58.734
I havena done anything to ye.

368
00:19:58.792 --> 00:20:01.519
JOAN: Daddy!
Ma! Stop!

369
00:20:01.699 --> 00:20:04.824
♪♪

370
00:20:05.566 --> 00:20:06.801
Daddy?

371
00:20:07.566 --> 00:20:09.589
LAOGHAIRE: [ scoffs ]

372
00:20:10.026 --> 00:20:11.895
He didna tell ye?

373
00:20:12.199 --> 00:20:15.214
He's my husband now.

374
00:20:16.300 --> 00:20:18.621
Have ye no shame.
you adulterous bitch?

375
00:20:18.690 --> 00:20:20.410
Go back to the hell
ye came from.

376
00:20:20.468 --> 00:20:22.128
Let me go!
Let the English cunt

377
00:20:22.230 --> 00:20:23.184
stand up for herself!

378
00:20:23.242 --> 00:20:24.384
Get yerself downstairs.
right now.

379
00:20:24.441 --> 00:20:25.985
LAOGHAIRE: Oh. get your hands
off me! Ugh!

380
00:20:26.042 --> 00:20:27.304
Oh. wait here.

381
00:20:27.510 --> 00:20:28.422
LAOGHAIRE: Can't believe
you did this to me!

382
00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:30.489
JAMIE: Laoghaire!
LAOGHAIRE: That woman!

383
00:20:30.719 --> 00:20:33.116
JAMIE: Laoghaire. wait!
LAOGHAIRE: With that witch!

384
00:20:33.216 --> 00:20:34.494
- [ exhales sharply ]
JOAN: Daddy!

385
00:20:34.551 --> 00:20:37.053
[ footsteps retreating ]

386
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:40.089
♪♪

387
00:20:40.578 --> 00:20:42.258
Who's that woman?

388
00:20:42.765 --> 00:20:44.928
Why'd she upset Ma so?

389
00:20:46.148 --> 00:20:49.296
Well. that woman is Claire.

390
00:20:50.641 --> 00:20:52.176
My wife.

391
00:20:54.781 --> 00:20:57.669
My... first wife.

392
00:21:07.984 --> 00:21:09.486
I thought she was dead.

393
00:21:09.586 --> 00:21:12.121
but by the grace of God.

394
00:21:12.221 --> 00:21:14.791
she came back to me.

395
00:21:14.891 --> 00:21:18.428
I-I planned on telling you
and your sister about her.

396
00:21:18.528 --> 00:21:21.665
but I didna get a chance.

397
00:21:21.765 --> 00:21:23.967
What about Ma?

398
00:21:25.335 --> 00:21:26.970
Well...

399
00:21:29.355 --> 00:21:32.277
I tried very hard
to be a husband to her.

400
00:21:32.394 --> 00:21:34.296
but your mother and I...

401
00:21:36.613 --> 00:21:38.768
We didna have a bond

402
00:21:38.949 --> 00:21:41.699
that keeps people together
forever.

403
00:21:42.050 --> 00:21:45.925
An' ye have that bond
wi' that other woman?

404
00:21:47.764 --> 00:21:49.232
Aye.

405
00:21:51.738 --> 00:21:55.589
Now. ye'll go away...

406
00:21:56.285 --> 00:21:57.972
forever?

407
00:21:58.434 --> 00:22:00.136
Dinna fash. Joanie.

408
00:22:00.527 --> 00:22:02.339
I love you and yer sister.

409
00:22:02.949 --> 00:22:05.375
I'll always look after ye.

410
00:22:07.144 --> 00:22:08.945
I promise.

411
00:22:09.089 --> 00:22:11.229
♪♪ Soft dramatic music...

412
00:22:11.448 --> 00:22:14.714
Now. go and find Marsali.

413
00:22:14.886 --> 00:22:16.320
She'll take ye home to yer ma.

414
00:22:16.378 --> 00:22:17.929
Go on.

415
00:22:17.987 --> 00:22:18.988
♪

416
00:22:19.190 --> 00:22:21.324
She needs ye.

417
00:22:22.183 --> 00:22:25.642
♪♪

418
00:22:28.320 --> 00:22:31.458
[ sobbing softly ]

419
00:22:34.111 --> 00:22:35.868
Claire.

420
00:22:37.180 --> 00:22:39.571
Will ye let me explain?

421
00:22:39.779 --> 00:22:42.556
- It's a little late for that.
- I dinna live with her.

422
00:22:42.790 --> 00:22:44.196
She and the girls live
at Balriggan.

423
00:22:44.261 --> 00:22:46.595
I-I didna think
they'd come here.

424
00:22:49.095 --> 00:22:51.296
It was a great mistake.
the marriage

425
00:22:51.354 --> 00:22:52.688
between Laoghaire and me.

426
00:22:52.923 --> 00:22:55.438
With two children?
That...

427
00:22:55.586 --> 00:22:58.813
took you quite a long time
to figure that out. didn't it?

428
00:22:59.126 --> 00:23:01.696
The lassies arna mine.
I-I'm not the father.

429
00:23:01.962 --> 00:23:03.509
Really?

430
00:23:03.634 --> 00:23:07.070
That little girl with...
the red hair?

431
00:23:07.170 --> 00:23:08.367
[ scoffs ]

432
00:23:08.425 --> 00:23:11.330
Well. there are other redheaded
men in Scotland. Claire.

433
00:23:11.388 --> 00:23:13.190
[ sniffles ]

434
00:23:13.784 --> 00:23:18.045
Look. Laoghaire was a-a-a widow
wi' two bairns when I wed her.

435
00:23:18.103 --> 00:23:19.288
It's been less than two years.

436
00:23:19.345 --> 00:23:20.908
and we've lived apart
most of that time.

437
00:23:20.970 --> 00:23:23.236
Oh. and I suppose that makes it
all right. does it?

438
00:23:25.561 --> 00:23:27.345
It's Laoghaire?

439
00:23:28.583 --> 00:23:31.806
She... she tried
to have me killed!

440
00:23:31.903 --> 00:23:35.314
Well. ye're the one that told me
to be kind to the lass!

441
00:23:38.173 --> 00:23:42.271
[ scoffs ]
I told you to thank her...

442
00:23:42.371 --> 00:23:43.673
not marry her.

443
00:23:43.869 --> 00:23:45.200
Ye're not going anywhere.

444
00:23:45.258 --> 00:23:47.267
You cannot stop me.

445
00:23:49.771 --> 00:23:51.462
You lied to me.

446
00:23:52.142 --> 00:23:55.619
You told me that you never
fell in love with anyone else.

447
00:23:56.070 --> 00:23:58.372
I didna fall in love.

448
00:23:59.155 --> 00:24:01.558
You told me about your son.

449
00:24:02.939 --> 00:24:05.479
Why couldn't you
tell me about this?

450
00:24:07.455 --> 00:24:08.923
Why?

451
00:24:09.413 --> 00:24:10.882
Why?

452
00:24:12.453 --> 00:24:14.291
Why?

453
00:24:15.579 --> 00:24:18.481
Because I am a coward.

454
00:24:20.278 --> 00:24:21.747
That's why.

455
00:24:22.435 --> 00:24:26.751
I couldna tell ye for fear
I would lose ye. and...

456
00:24:27.646 --> 00:24:29.787
I couldna bear the thought
of losing you again.

457
00:24:29.928 --> 00:24:32.529
I wanted you so badly
that nothing else mattered.

458
00:24:32.662 --> 00:24:36.435
I would sacrifice honor. family.
l-life itself to see you.

459
00:24:36.529 --> 00:24:39.629
to lie with you again.
even though you left me.

460
00:24:43.967 --> 00:24:45.638
Left you?

461
00:24:49.320 --> 00:24:51.365
Left you?

462
00:24:52.709 --> 00:24:55.537
You forced me to go back!

463
00:24:55.931 --> 00:25:00.513
I would have died gladly
at Culloden with you.

464
00:25:01.098 --> 00:25:03.222
And now you want to blame me
for that?

465
00:25:03.280 --> 00:25:05.148
I dinna blame you for it.

466
00:25:05.453 --> 00:25:07.443
Ye had to go for Brianna's sake.

467
00:25:07.592 --> 00:25:09.459
I c-canna regret that.

468
00:25:13.098 --> 00:25:14.763
But you blame me
for coming back.

469
00:25:14.821 --> 00:25:16.271
No.

470
00:25:16.329 --> 00:25:17.964
Yes.

471
00:25:18.301 --> 00:25:21.170
No.
[ sighs ]

472
00:25:21.270 --> 00:25:23.139
God. no. I...

473
00:25:24.540 --> 00:25:26.576
Do ye know what it is
to live 20 years

474
00:25:26.676 --> 00:25:28.247
wi'out a heart?

475
00:25:28.332 --> 00:25:32.166
To live half a man
and accustom yourself

476
00:25:32.274 --> 00:25:34.421
to exist in the bit
that's left?

477
00:25:34.484 --> 00:25:36.241
Do I know?

478
00:25:36.419 --> 00:25:37.654
Do I know how that feels?

479
00:25:37.754 --> 00:25:39.656
Yes. you bastard. I know!

480
00:25:39.756 --> 00:25:41.702
What did you think.
that I went back to Frank

481
00:25:41.760 --> 00:25:43.693
and lived happily ever after?

482
00:25:43.793 --> 00:25:45.268
Sometimes. I hoped ye did.

483
00:25:45.438 --> 00:25:47.173
And sometimes. I could see it...

484
00:25:47.231 --> 00:25:48.851
Him with you.
day and night.

485
00:25:48.909 --> 00:25:50.233
lying with ye.
taking your body.

486
00:25:50.333 --> 00:25:51.467
holding my bairn!

487
00:25:51.567 --> 00:25:53.670
And God.
I could kill ye for it!

488
00:25:53.762 --> 00:25:55.760
Well. I don't have
to imagine Laoghaire!

489
00:25:55.854 --> 00:25:57.047
Laoghaire?

490
00:25:57.284 --> 00:25:58.870
Christ!

491
00:25:58.943 --> 00:26:00.952
I dinna care about Laoghaire.
and I never have!

492
00:26:01.010 --> 00:26:02.789
Oh. so you would marry a woman
you don't even want

493
00:26:02.846 --> 00:26:04.657
and then just discard her
the second you're done?

494
00:26:04.714 --> 00:26:06.249
No. I'm damned
one way or the other.

495
00:26:06.349 --> 00:26:08.846
If I felt anything for her.
I'm a faithless lecher.

496
00:26:08.904 --> 00:26:10.687
and if I didn't.
I'm a heartless beast!

497
00:26:10.802 --> 00:26:12.643
Well. you should have told me.

498
00:26:12.701 --> 00:26:14.893
And if I had.
ye would've turned on your heel

499
00:26:14.956 --> 00:26:16.362
and left without a word.

500
00:26:16.702 --> 00:26:18.081
But having seen you again.

501
00:26:18.159 --> 00:26:21.530
I would do far worse than lie
to keep you!

502
00:26:21.631 --> 00:26:22.966
♪♪ Dramatic music...

503
00:26:23.066 --> 00:26:25.368
[ grunting ]

504
00:26:25.476 --> 00:26:27.511
[ grunting ]

505
00:26:27.603 --> 00:26:29.114
Get off me!

506
00:26:29.172 --> 00:26:32.074
[ both grunting ]

507
00:26:32.595 --> 00:26:34.842
- Claire! Claire!
- No!

508
00:26:34.900 --> 00:26:37.678
Claire. I-I love you
and only you.

509
00:26:37.914 --> 00:26:40.884
♪♪

510
00:26:43.853 --> 00:26:46.923
[ both moaning and panting ]

511
00:26:57.920 --> 00:26:59.357
JENNY: Stop it!

512
00:26:59.461 --> 00:27:00.803
Both of ye.

513
00:27:01.427 --> 00:27:03.597
Fightin' and ruttin'
like wild beasts.

514
00:27:03.655 --> 00:27:06.658
and no carin'
if the whole house hears ye!

515
00:27:06.910 --> 00:27:10.467
♪♪

516
00:27:35.794 --> 00:27:38.098
JANET: Would ye like a whisky?

517
00:27:40.911 --> 00:27:43.312
Suppose I could do with one.

518
00:27:54.914 --> 00:27:56.848
Thank you.

519
00:27:59.520 --> 00:28:03.833
I apologize for...
disturbing the household.

520
00:28:05.634 --> 00:28:07.370
I should be apologizin' to you.

521
00:28:09.783 --> 00:28:11.658
I told Auntie Laoghaire
ye were here.

522
00:28:11.900 --> 00:28:12.976
That's why she came.

523
00:28:14.768 --> 00:28:17.659
I didna have it in mind
tae cause such a kebbie-lebbie.

524
00:28:17.746 --> 00:28:19.048
Truly not.

525
00:28:19.933 --> 00:28:21.109
Well. I suppose one of us

526
00:28:21.167 --> 00:28:23.464
would have found out
sooner or later.

527
00:28:30.232 --> 00:28:32.000
Why did you tell her?

528
00:28:34.521 --> 00:28:36.027
Mother told me to.

529
00:28:36.308 --> 00:28:38.835
[ footsteps approaching ]

530
00:28:41.838 --> 00:28:44.205
You told Laoghaire to come?

531
00:28:44.673 --> 00:28:45.842
She's his wife.

532
00:28:45.942 --> 00:28:48.244
I am his wife.

533
00:28:48.455 --> 00:28:51.478
Then why'd ye no try
to find him after the war?

534
00:28:52.081 --> 00:28:54.851
And why'd it take ye 20 years
to come back here?

535
00:28:54.951 --> 00:28:56.752
Because I thought he was dead.

536
00:28:56.853 --> 00:28:58.554
In a way. he was.

537
00:28:58.654 --> 00:29:00.890
Took him an age
to start livin' again.

538
00:29:00.990 --> 00:29:02.859
and now you're back
no more than a week.

539
00:29:02.959 --> 00:29:04.759
and ye've killed a man.
his print shop's razed

540
00:29:04.828 --> 00:29:06.038
to the ground. and he's
on the run from the law.

541
00:29:06.095 --> 00:29:08.031
I suppose that's all my doing?

542
00:29:08.131 --> 00:29:09.716
Well. there's no denyin'
trouble finds my brother.

543
00:29:09.773 --> 00:29:11.876
but ye didna help matters much.

544
00:29:11.968 --> 00:29:15.041
I wanted to come back
to be part of this family again.

545
00:29:15.307 --> 00:29:18.507
Well. family writes letters.

546
00:29:18.728 --> 00:29:21.564
Telling one another
they're alive.

547
00:29:22.025 --> 00:29:24.513
What. d'ye think
we were all just frozen in time

548
00:29:24.571 --> 00:29:26.407
waiting for you to return?

549
00:29:26.549 --> 00:29:27.851
No.

550
00:29:28.435 --> 00:29:30.170
Look. I...

551
00:29:30.270 --> 00:29:33.574
I had another husband
in America.

552
00:29:34.065 --> 00:29:36.221
and it was a matter of survival.

553
00:29:36.342 --> 00:29:37.535
Now. it wasn't easy.

554
00:29:37.593 --> 00:29:39.978
but I had to put
my past behind me

555
00:29:40.230 --> 00:29:42.650
so that I could make
that marriage work.

556
00:29:47.764 --> 00:29:49.099
Does Jamie know?

557
00:29:49.611 --> 00:29:50.974
Yes.

558
00:29:52.809 --> 00:29:54.510
Did ye have any bairns?

559
00:29:54.643 --> 00:29:56.479
No.

560
00:29:57.947 --> 00:30:00.816
I never had children with him.

561
00:30:02.188 --> 00:30:04.256
But when he died.

562
00:30:04.512 --> 00:30:06.314
I decided to come back

563
00:30:06.563 --> 00:30:07.967
to visit Jamie's grave.

564
00:30:08.025 --> 00:30:11.861
to tell him
that I never forgot him.

565
00:30:13.344 --> 00:30:15.681
But instead. I found him alive.

566
00:30:20.698 --> 00:30:23.314
I hear truth in what
ye're tellin' me.

567
00:30:24.291 --> 00:30:26.018
But I can see it in yer eyes.
there's still something

568
00:30:26.075 --> 00:30:28.377
ye're keepin' from me.

569
00:30:29.081 --> 00:30:31.397
I don't know
if I can or even want

570
00:30:31.455 --> 00:30:33.502
to put my trust
in you again.

571
00:30:33.887 --> 00:30:35.488
When a horse breaks its leg.

572
00:30:35.546 --> 00:30:36.794
ye put it out of its misery

573
00:30:36.852 --> 00:30:38.986
because it'll never heal right.

574
00:30:40.243 --> 00:30:42.212
Neither will we.

575
00:30:56.139 --> 00:30:57.673
If my mother was still alive.

576
00:30:57.773 --> 00:31:00.002
this would kill her
all over again.

577
00:31:00.283 --> 00:31:02.228
Jamie's retired to the stables.

578
00:31:02.304 --> 00:31:06.088
and Janet's given Claire
blankets in the guest chamber.

579
00:31:06.588 --> 00:31:08.851
[ stammers ]
This doesna bother you?

580
00:31:08.952 --> 00:31:10.572
Him laying wi' both wives?

581
00:31:10.684 --> 00:31:12.663
He and Laoghaire
are not living as man and wife.

582
00:31:12.721 --> 00:31:13.731
and ye ken it.

583
00:31:13.789 --> 00:31:15.091
He makes a fool of this family.

584
00:31:15.191 --> 00:31:17.572
IAN: Ye're the only one
being foolish.

585
00:31:17.630 --> 00:31:19.365
If there's a pot of shite on
to boil.

586
00:31:19.471 --> 00:31:22.267
ye stir like it's God's work.

587
00:31:22.325 --> 00:31:23.705
Oh. this is my fault then?

588
00:31:23.955 --> 00:31:26.689
D'ye forget I hear
yer prayers every night?

589
00:31:27.074 --> 00:31:28.943
And all ye ask for
is Jamie's happiness.

590
00:31:29.016 --> 00:31:31.103
after all the sorrows he's seen.

591
00:31:31.385 --> 00:31:35.072
and here he is.
but ye canna let him have it.

592
00:31:41.929 --> 00:31:44.898
Does this look like happiness
to you?

593
00:31:47.731 --> 00:31:50.701
♪♪

594
00:31:57.366 --> 00:32:00.469
♪♪

595
00:32:04.904 --> 00:32:06.193
JAMIE: Claire.

596
00:32:06.521 --> 00:32:08.092
Claire.

597
00:32:09.099 --> 00:32:10.537
JAMIE: Please.

598
00:32:10.743 --> 00:32:13.217
I should never have come back.

599
00:32:13.715 --> 00:32:16.084
Canna take back
those 20 years...

600
00:32:23.573 --> 00:32:25.042
Or the life I've lived.

601
00:32:25.323 --> 00:32:27.479
But I mean
to make things right.

602
00:32:27.708 --> 00:32:29.978
I knew coming back was a risk.

603
00:32:30.463 --> 00:32:32.057
That you could be
a different person.

604
00:32:32.135 --> 00:32:33.645
that we both could be
different people. but...

605
00:32:33.702 --> 00:32:36.605
I'm still the same person
you fell in love with.

606
00:32:38.424 --> 00:32:42.878
"When you tell me something.
let it be the truth.

607
00:32:43.343 --> 00:32:45.813
and I promise you the same."

608
00:32:46.155 --> 00:32:48.590
Those were your words. Jamie.

609
00:32:50.012 --> 00:32:53.982
We could have secrets.
but not lies.

610
00:32:54.223 --> 00:32:57.660
I'm sorry. Claire.
Truly.

611
00:32:57.760 --> 00:32:59.651
♪♪

612
00:32:59.951 --> 00:33:04.422
I've only known
one love in my life.

613
00:33:04.737 --> 00:33:07.070
And that was with you.

614
00:33:07.245 --> 00:33:08.827
LAOGHAIRE:
There's the truth of it then?

615
00:33:08.885 --> 00:33:09.924
[ gun clicks ]

616
00:33:10.026 --> 00:33:11.080
Oh. God. Laoghaire.

617
00:33:11.190 --> 00:33:12.675
Laoghaire.
p-put the pistol down.

618
00:33:12.733 --> 00:33:13.934
No.

619
00:33:14.077 --> 00:33:15.157
I will not just sit at home

620
00:33:15.244 --> 00:33:18.314
and let her walk away with ye.

621
00:33:18.893 --> 00:33:20.557
I've come to protect
what's mine.

622
00:33:20.651 --> 00:33:22.362
This isna Claire's fault.

623
00:33:22.542 --> 00:33:24.104
Time for her to leave us be.

624
00:33:24.284 --> 00:33:26.155
To stay out of our lives.

625
00:33:26.255 --> 00:33:28.390
You and I have not dwelt
in the same house

626
00:33:28.448 --> 00:33:30.409
for... many a month.

627
00:33:30.503 --> 00:33:32.628
Mebbe it wasna perfect.

628
00:33:33.220 --> 00:33:34.590
but you were mine.

629
00:33:35.199 --> 00:33:36.568
If not under my roof.

630
00:33:36.745 --> 00:33:37.633
ye provided for me and...

631
00:33:37.733 --> 00:33:39.135
[ both scream ]

632
00:33:39.235 --> 00:33:40.436
JAMIE: [ groans ]

633
00:33:40.536 --> 00:33:41.637
CLAIRE: [ grunts ]

634
00:33:41.737 --> 00:33:43.073
Jamie!

635
00:33:43.131 --> 00:33:45.767
- Aah!
- Get away from him!

636
00:33:46.242 --> 00:33:48.611
JAMIE: [ groaning ]
- [ crying ]

637
00:33:49.140 --> 00:33:50.542
Jamie!

638
00:33:52.547 --> 00:33:54.119
CLAIRE:
Help me get him onto the table.

639
00:33:54.177 --> 00:33:55.861
Och. what's a few more scars?

640
00:33:55.919 --> 00:33:57.779
Leave me be.
I'm just fine.

641
00:33:57.895 --> 00:33:59.247
Get me some alcohol. please.

642
00:33:59.355 --> 00:34:01.885
Here.
Take this off.

643
00:34:01.943 --> 00:34:04.059
[ groaning ]

644
00:34:04.708 --> 00:34:06.262
Take your shirt off.

645
00:34:06.362 --> 00:34:08.063
[ indistinct chatter ]

646
00:34:08.172 --> 00:34:09.506
[ grunting ]

647
00:34:09.564 --> 00:34:10.865
Oh. dear God.

648
00:34:11.288 --> 00:34:13.013
Who did this?

649
00:34:13.836 --> 00:34:14.937
Laoghaire.

650
00:34:15.939 --> 00:34:17.904
It's nothing Claire canna fix.

651
00:34:18.481 --> 00:34:20.557
I'll get clean towels
and bandages.

652
00:34:20.623 --> 00:34:21.802
Go get my medical kit.

653
00:34:21.872 --> 00:34:23.247
It's in my bag in the courtyard.

654
00:34:23.305 --> 00:34:24.408
Yeah.

655
00:34:24.466 --> 00:34:25.275
Can you get hot water

656
00:34:25.333 --> 00:34:26.487
and see if you can find
an apron?

657
00:34:26.544 --> 00:34:27.416
Aye.

658
00:34:27.516 --> 00:34:30.419
It's only bird shot.
Nothing serious.

659
00:34:30.544 --> 00:34:32.597
Have you forgot
what I told you about germs?

660
00:34:32.655 --> 00:34:34.257
Aye. thank you.

661
00:34:34.560 --> 00:34:36.779
- I'll help my father.
- Here.

662
00:34:36.982 --> 00:34:38.779
I'm going to have to dig
those pellets out.

663
00:34:38.864 --> 00:34:40.833
- Ah.
- Mm.

664
00:34:41.164 --> 00:34:43.732
[ both panting ]

665
00:34:44.222 --> 00:34:45.990
- Lie down.
- Mm.

666
00:34:47.069 --> 00:34:48.937
♪

667
00:34:49.045 --> 00:34:50.914
[ grunts ]

668
00:34:51.006 --> 00:34:54.177
♪

669
00:35:04.320 --> 00:35:05.654
[ pellet clinks ]

670
00:35:05.754 --> 00:35:08.491
♪

671
00:35:08.747 --> 00:35:11.560
Those're very fancy knives
ye've got there. Auntie.

672
00:35:15.427 --> 00:35:19.568
I. uh. I knew a very fine cutler
in the Colonies.

673
00:35:19.904 --> 00:35:22.070
CLAIRE: Mm.
JAMIE: [ grunts softly ]

674
00:35:22.171 --> 00:35:23.206
♪

675
00:35:23.306 --> 00:35:25.208
[ pellet clinks ]

676
00:35:25.308 --> 00:35:27.786
All right. this is the one
I'm worried about.

677
00:35:27.911 --> 00:35:29.700
If the pellets penetrated
the artery.

678
00:35:29.758 --> 00:35:30.848
then you'll bleed to death.

679
00:35:30.906 --> 00:35:32.954
and there'll be nothing
I can do about it.

680
00:35:34.717 --> 00:35:37.586
♪♪

681
00:35:39.555 --> 00:35:40.723
[ groans ]

682
00:35:45.394 --> 00:35:46.729
[ cork squeaks and pops ]

683
00:35:46.829 --> 00:35:49.097
[ softly grunts ]

684
00:35:49.198 --> 00:35:52.335
♪♪

685
00:35:53.910 --> 00:35:55.571
JAMIE: [ grunts ]

686
00:35:55.671 --> 00:35:58.641
♪♪

687
00:35:59.842 --> 00:36:01.377
[ grunts ]

688
00:36:01.477 --> 00:36:04.447
♪♪

689
00:36:09.885 --> 00:36:11.119
CLAIRE: [ exhales sharply ]

690
00:36:11.220 --> 00:36:13.291
[ sighs ]

691
00:36:13.986 --> 00:36:16.447
Did it penetrate the... artery?

692
00:36:16.666 --> 00:36:19.127
No.
He was very lucky.

693
00:36:19.361 --> 00:36:20.361
[ sighs ]

694
00:36:20.627 --> 00:36:22.465
[ cork squeaks and pops ]

695
00:36:22.565 --> 00:36:25.534
♪♪

696
00:36:43.677 --> 00:36:44.812
Auntie.

697
00:36:47.052 --> 00:36:49.064
Eh. he has enough alcohol
for now.

698
00:36:49.122 --> 00:36:51.694
- Thank you.
- It's not for Uncle Jamie.

699
00:36:51.794 --> 00:36:53.716
It's for you. Auntie.

700
00:36:57.800 --> 00:36:59.202
[ cork squeaks and pops ]

701
00:36:59.260 --> 00:37:01.388
You're the only one
who calls me that.

702
00:37:02.705 --> 00:37:03.705
[ cork squeaks ]

703
00:37:05.474 --> 00:37:08.511
♪♪ Soft dramatic music...

704
00:37:08.611 --> 00:37:11.414
♪♪

705
00:37:11.886 --> 00:37:13.882
Uncle Jamie's lucky
you're here.

706
00:37:16.707 --> 00:37:19.677
♪♪

707
00:37:38.474 --> 00:37:40.576
JAMIE: [ sighs ]

708
00:37:49.952 --> 00:37:51.354
[ grunts softly ]

709
00:37:57.412 --> 00:37:59.647
She made a nice Swiss cheese
of your arm.

710
00:37:59.728 --> 00:38:01.699
I dinna ken
what Swiss cheese is.

711
00:38:01.757 --> 00:38:05.859
but if it looks like that.
I wouldna want it on my bread.

712
00:38:06.148 --> 00:38:08.571
Well. the pellets are out.

713
00:38:09.046 --> 00:38:11.116
and your artery's intact.

714
00:38:16.007 --> 00:38:17.402
I need a whisky.

715
00:38:17.484 --> 00:38:18.881
You've had enough.

716
00:38:19.202 --> 00:38:20.702
You need liquids.

717
00:38:20.914 --> 00:38:22.282
Water or broth.

718
00:38:23.109 --> 00:38:24.882
Whisky's a liquid. no?

719
00:38:25.226 --> 00:38:26.851
No.
Here.

720
00:38:27.096 --> 00:38:28.998
Drink this.

721
00:38:44.937 --> 00:38:48.509
I'll never understand
what you saw in that woman.

722
00:38:49.126 --> 00:38:53.090
Well. she wasna toting a pistol
when I chanced upon her again.

723
00:38:53.462 --> 00:38:55.384
That's it?

724
00:38:56.118 --> 00:38:57.853
You truly wish to hear?

725
00:38:59.579 --> 00:39:01.490
You won't get angry?

726
00:39:04.798 --> 00:39:07.463
I haven't stopped being angry.

727
00:39:10.134 --> 00:39:12.634
So you might as well
explain yourself.

728
00:39:16.306 --> 00:39:18.407
I'd been away so long.

729
00:39:19.743 --> 00:39:22.517
When I returned from Helwater.

730
00:39:23.524 --> 00:39:25.648
from England.

731
00:39:26.102 --> 00:39:29.196
everything was... different.

732
00:39:29.727 --> 00:39:32.267
Jenny's bairns
didn't recognize me.

733
00:39:34.274 --> 00:39:35.924
I was a ghost.

734
00:39:38.517 --> 00:39:39.946
If ye ken what I mean.

735
00:39:41.993 --> 00:39:45.142
Yes... I do.

736
00:39:45.587 --> 00:39:50.056
I was here...
but I wasna home.

737
00:39:50.876 --> 00:39:52.227
[ grunts softly ]

738
00:39:57.861 --> 00:39:59.829
I suppose I was lonely.

739
00:40:01.087 --> 00:40:05.854
It was my first Hogmanay
at Lallybroch

740
00:40:06.095 --> 00:40:08.223
since I was a lad.

741
00:40:08.323 --> 00:40:09.692
Hee-yo!

742
00:40:09.970 --> 00:40:13.915
JAMIE: Everything about
Lallybroch was shining. warm.

743
00:40:14.229 --> 00:40:16.431
Jenny had dressed the parlor.

744
00:40:16.532 --> 00:40:17.933
Never seen it so bonny.

745
00:40:18.033 --> 00:40:20.302
The fiddler
was by the window there.

746
00:40:20.402 --> 00:40:21.904
playing jigs and reels.

747
00:40:22.157 --> 00:40:25.908
Every table laden
wi' food. drink.

748
00:40:26.234 --> 00:40:28.188
I could feel
my father and mother there

749
00:40:28.259 --> 00:40:30.251
and... my brother Willie.

750
00:40:30.546 --> 00:40:33.783
I was filled with joy and
loneliness at the same time.

751
00:40:34.016 --> 00:40:36.719
[ cheering ]

752
00:40:36.819 --> 00:40:38.453
♪♪

753
00:40:38.554 --> 00:40:40.889
JOAN: Do you like figs?

754
00:40:41.095 --> 00:40:42.691
[ girls giggle ]

755
00:40:43.782 --> 00:40:44.893
Aye.

756
00:40:45.063 --> 00:40:46.161
Thank you.

757
00:40:46.219 --> 00:40:47.353
[ laughter ]

758
00:40:47.411 --> 00:40:48.797
Would you like to dance?

759
00:40:48.897 --> 00:40:50.733
[ cheering ]

760
00:40:50.825 --> 00:40:53.027
It's been a very long time
since I tried.

761
00:40:53.135 --> 00:40:55.470
We can teach you.

762
00:40:55.571 --> 00:40:57.072
[ girls chuckling ]

763
00:40:57.172 --> 00:40:58.941
[ festive violin music ]

764
00:40:59.041 --> 00:41:00.976
[ girls laugh ]

765
00:41:01.076 --> 00:41:04.046
♪♪

766
00:41:04.146 --> 00:41:07.015
[ cheering ]

767
00:41:07.115 --> 00:41:08.483
[ girls giggling ]

768
00:41:08.584 --> 00:41:11.419
♪♪ Sentimental music. ..

769
00:41:11.512 --> 00:41:14.649
♪♪

770
00:41:22.064 --> 00:41:25.023
JAMIE: After a few moments.
my heart felt lighter.

771
00:41:25.125 --> 00:41:28.477
The music wrapped around me.
and I was laughing.

772
00:41:31.964 --> 00:41:36.735
I realized I hadna truly
laughed since that last time...

773
00:41:36.945 --> 00:41:40.115
well. the last time
I was with you.

774
00:41:40.215 --> 00:41:42.117
♪♪ Festive violin music...

775
00:41:42.217 --> 00:41:45.120
[ laughter and chatter ]

776
00:41:45.220 --> 00:41:48.123
[ cheers and applause ]

777
00:41:54.763 --> 00:41:56.198
[ indistinct chatter ]

778
00:41:56.298 --> 00:41:57.298
Whew!

779
00:41:57.365 --> 00:41:59.467
[ festive violin music ]

780
00:41:59.568 --> 00:42:01.303
Ye're a bonny dancer.

781
00:42:01.696 --> 00:42:04.068
- Thank you. So are you.
- Ha!

782
00:42:04.126 --> 00:42:05.507
Ye've fair worked up
my appetite.

783
00:42:05.608 --> 00:42:07.576
[ chuckles ]

784
00:42:07.676 --> 00:42:09.011
You Cousin Aileen's daughters?

785
00:42:09.111 --> 00:42:13.148
No. Our mother
is Mistress MacKimmie.

786
00:42:13.248 --> 00:42:16.585
♪♪

787
00:42:18.571 --> 00:42:21.540
♪♪ Dramatic music...

788
00:42:21.892 --> 00:42:23.931
JAMIE: So there she was.

789
00:42:24.226 --> 00:42:28.345
Twice widowed and two bairns
aching for a father.

790
00:42:28.633 --> 00:42:30.626
That was plain enough.

791
00:42:30.866 --> 00:42:34.436
I found something
to fill the hole I had in me.

792
00:42:34.712 --> 00:42:36.626
Jenny kent it as well.

793
00:42:36.810 --> 00:42:39.712
Urged me to make the match.

794
00:42:40.142 --> 00:42:42.110
I wanted to be a...

795
00:42:42.611 --> 00:42:46.134
a father. a husband...

796
00:42:47.015 --> 00:42:49.313
all the things I thought
the future held

797
00:42:49.407 --> 00:42:51.165
when I was with you.

798
00:42:52.285 --> 00:42:55.121
All the things I had to forget

799
00:42:55.462 --> 00:42:57.793
when I said good-bye to you
at the stones.

800
00:43:00.196 --> 00:43:04.633
To care for Willie or Brianna...

801
00:43:06.220 --> 00:43:07.722
Watch them grow up.

802
00:43:08.118 --> 00:43:11.674
to show them how to be
in the world.

803
00:43:13.524 --> 00:43:16.211
I thought
if I married Laoghaire.

804
00:43:16.493 --> 00:43:18.431
I could have all those things.

805
00:43:22.248 --> 00:43:23.805
And did you?

806
00:43:25.352 --> 00:43:29.692
My fondness
for Marsali and Joan grew.

807
00:43:31.806 --> 00:43:33.842
It was a very special time
for me.

808
00:43:35.664 --> 00:43:37.065
And not always easy...

809
00:43:37.165 --> 00:43:38.934
[ grunts softly ]

810
00:43:39.243 --> 00:43:41.737
[ exhales and grunts ]
But...

811
00:43:41.795 --> 00:43:44.351
it was all right.

812
00:43:44.409 --> 00:43:46.778
[ groans softly ]

813
00:43:46.861 --> 00:43:49.263
[ sighs ]

814
00:43:49.581 --> 00:43:51.977
So then what happened?

815
00:43:53.289 --> 00:43:56.720
How did you end up
living in Edinburgh?

816
00:43:57.462 --> 00:43:59.259
There were days...

817
00:43:59.461 --> 00:44:01.597
weeks where she
wouldn't speak with me.

818
00:44:02.111 --> 00:44:04.908
To be honest.
I-I didn't mind that.

819
00:44:05.299 --> 00:44:08.041
Meant we wouldn't be fighting
over this or that.

820
00:44:08.502 --> 00:44:10.933
[ sighs and grunts ]

821
00:44:11.033 --> 00:44:13.354
I tried to be gentle wi' her.

822
00:44:13.736 --> 00:44:16.138
but it was no use.

823
00:44:16.604 --> 00:44:18.640
Maybe it was
her first husband. Hugh.

824
00:44:18.741 --> 00:44:23.674
or... her second husband. Simon.

825
00:44:24.536 --> 00:44:27.905
Well. nobody kens what happens
in the marriage bed.

826
00:44:30.015 --> 00:44:31.950
She was hurt.

827
00:44:32.369 --> 00:44:35.354
I could see the fear
in her eyes.

828
00:44:36.331 --> 00:44:37.666
So I left.

829
00:44:37.947 --> 00:44:40.362
♪♪ Somber music...

830
00:44:40.893 --> 00:44:43.159
I couldn't bear
the thought of...

831
00:44:43.268 --> 00:44:46.120
someone being afraid
of my touch.

832
00:44:46.257 --> 00:44:49.227
♪♪

833
00:44:59.381 --> 00:45:01.283
Christ...

834
00:45:01.383 --> 00:45:02.680
you're burning up.

835
00:45:02.738 --> 00:45:04.439
Huh?

836
00:45:04.612 --> 00:45:06.413
Why on earth
didn't you say something?

837
00:45:06.576 --> 00:45:07.912
Huh.

838
00:45:08.891 --> 00:45:11.293
I thought
it was the heat of shame.

839
00:45:13.778 --> 00:45:16.489
If you won't stay with me.
then I'd rather die

840
00:45:16.547 --> 00:45:18.967
and be done with it
if that's all the same with you.

841
00:45:19.067 --> 00:45:23.872
I'm not going to let you die.
tempted as I might be.

842
00:45:23.972 --> 00:45:26.074
[ objects clinking ]

843
00:45:31.279 --> 00:45:33.148
[ panting softly ]

844
00:45:36.086 --> 00:45:37.969
What in God's name is that?

845
00:45:38.102 --> 00:45:41.056
Something that will help
bring down your fever.

846
00:45:48.197 --> 00:45:50.800
Now. roll over
onto your right side.

847
00:45:52.843 --> 00:45:55.145
Uh...
[ grunts ]

848
00:45:55.203 --> 00:45:56.638
Yeah. that...

849
00:45:56.696 --> 00:45:59.062
that. uh.
that looks mighty sharp.

850
00:45:59.133 --> 00:46:02.109
It is. so you better
hold still and relax.

851
00:46:02.297 --> 00:46:05.213
Look. will ye please explain
why jabbing needles

852
00:46:05.313 --> 00:46:10.252
in my arse
is going to help my arm?

853
00:46:10.625 --> 00:46:14.122
Because germs are no match
for penicillin.

854
00:46:23.946 --> 00:46:25.734
[ grunts softly ]

855
00:46:26.101 --> 00:46:29.171
[ footsteps approaching ]

856
00:46:39.531 --> 00:46:42.070
I had a vision of ye. ye ken.

857
00:46:43.102 --> 00:46:44.819
When Jamie wed Laoghaire.

858
00:46:44.920 --> 00:46:47.211
them standing by the altar.

859
00:46:47.789 --> 00:46:50.062
ye were there wi' them.

860
00:46:50.848 --> 00:46:53.117
standin' betwixt him
and Laoghaire.

861
00:46:58.195 --> 00:47:02.187
I didna ken who ye were or what.

862
00:47:02.625 --> 00:47:06.141
We didna know
your people or your place.

863
00:47:06.241 --> 00:47:08.210
Even when Jamie told me
you might tell me things

864
00:47:08.310 --> 00:47:11.617
that might no make any sense.
I didna question it.

865
00:47:12.108 --> 00:47:15.141
Ye said plant potatoes.
I did as told.

866
00:47:15.417 --> 00:47:16.594
The crop kept us alive

867
00:47:16.664 --> 00:47:18.465
for more than one winter
after Culloden.

868
00:47:18.546 --> 00:47:19.811
You saved us.
and I never asked ye

869
00:47:19.868 --> 00:47:21.852
about any of it. did I?

870
00:47:21.990 --> 00:47:25.293
Jamie chose ye.
That was enough.

871
00:47:29.911 --> 00:47:32.280
But it's not enough now.
is it?

872
00:47:35.101 --> 00:47:37.904
I suppose ye'll never
tell me the full story.

873
00:47:46.656 --> 00:47:49.477
What I can tell you...

874
00:47:50.352 --> 00:47:53.922
is that I love your brother
very much.

875
00:47:54.422 --> 00:47:56.727
I never forgot him.

876
00:47:58.493 --> 00:48:00.528
Or any of you.

877
00:48:04.007 --> 00:48:06.910
I never stopped wearing
his wedding ring.

878
00:48:08.128 --> 00:48:10.531
You were a sister to me.

879
00:48:11.013 --> 00:48:13.731
♪♪ Pensive music...

880
00:48:13.942 --> 00:48:17.079
♪♪

881
00:48:17.912 --> 00:48:20.081
I loved you too. Jenny.

882
00:48:20.543 --> 00:48:23.118
Still do.

883
00:48:24.883 --> 00:48:27.852
I'm only asking
for a second chance.

884
00:48:36.529 --> 00:48:39.498
♪♪

885
00:48:46.555 --> 00:48:48.862
- [ gasps ]
- Oh. my dear.

886
00:48:48.920 --> 00:48:50.681
Is it truly you?

887
00:48:50.813 --> 00:48:52.649
Oh. Ned!

888
00:48:52.772 --> 00:48:53.839
[ laughs ]

889
00:48:53.917 --> 00:48:55.753
Oh. w-what are you doing here?

890
00:48:55.914 --> 00:48:59.017
Well. I've-I've come
to speak to your husband.

891
00:48:59.321 --> 00:49:01.032
Oh!

892
00:49:01.748 --> 00:49:05.298
You're-you're a feast
for these old eyes.

893
00:49:05.403 --> 00:49:06.870
[ both chuckle ]

894
00:49:06.928 --> 00:49:09.030
Pardon me.
I'm...

895
00:49:09.205 --> 00:49:11.107
I'm a trifle overcome.

896
00:49:11.199 --> 00:49:13.126
You look exactly the same.

897
00:49:13.236 --> 00:49:15.001
What is your secret?

898
00:49:15.103 --> 00:49:18.423
Well. I never married.
[ laughs ]

899
00:49:19.251 --> 00:49:23.289
Well. with the return
of the first Mrs. James Fraser.

900
00:49:23.603 --> 00:49:26.948
legally. the marriage
to Laoghaire MacKimmie

901
00:49:27.049 --> 00:49:28.657
is invalid.

902
00:49:28.715 --> 00:49:30.969
Eh. you'll have to make
reconciliations

903
00:49:31.027 --> 00:49:32.329
with the Church. mind ye.

904
00:49:32.387 --> 00:49:34.022
Oh. it's a price
I'm willing to pay.

905
00:49:34.122 --> 00:49:35.657
Funny you should mention that.

906
00:49:35.757 --> 00:49:39.061
Laoghaire has made a complaint
to the Justice of the Peace.

907
00:49:39.161 --> 00:49:41.860
uh. for distress
and loss of support.

908
00:49:41.954 --> 00:49:43.040
How could she do that?

909
00:49:43.098 --> 00:49:44.466
"nor hell a fury

910
00:49:44.566 --> 00:49:46.063
like a woman scorned."

911
00:49:46.332 --> 00:49:47.367
Hm.

912
00:49:47.452 --> 00:49:49.187
But she shot him.

913
00:49:49.404 --> 00:49:51.939
Indeed. and in the Highlands.

914
00:49:52.047 --> 00:49:54.349
as we know.
Disarming Act means

915
00:49:54.442 --> 00:49:58.346
that owning a firearm
is a criminal offense.

916
00:49:58.446 --> 00:50:01.220
NED: Now.
where is the weapon now?

917
00:50:02.138 --> 00:50:04.556
Young Jamie has it hidden
in the stables.

918
00:50:04.614 --> 00:50:07.551
Any way of proving
that it belongs to Laoghaire?

919
00:50:07.609 --> 00:50:09.367
Well. besides myself and Claire
bearing witness

920
00:50:09.424 --> 00:50:13.795
and the five holes
in my arm... no.

921
00:50:14.282 --> 00:50:16.845
Well. uh.
if it proceeds to trial

922
00:50:16.903 --> 00:50:18.438
and you're summoned to court.

923
00:50:18.800 --> 00:50:21.203
she may be indicted.

924
00:50:21.303 --> 00:50:24.038
Uh. we could arrange
for the weapon

925
00:50:24.139 --> 00:50:26.941
to be turned over
to the British.

926
00:50:27.041 --> 00:50:28.543
And what would happen to her?

927
00:50:28.643 --> 00:50:31.045
If found guilty.
she could be transported

928
00:50:31.146 --> 00:50:32.680
to the Colonies.

929
00:50:32.780 --> 00:50:34.616
Virginia. most likely.

930
00:50:36.328 --> 00:50:38.864
I do hear Richmond is nice
this time of year.

931
00:50:38.922 --> 00:50:40.223
Hmm.
Indeed.

932
00:50:42.111 --> 00:50:44.337
No.

933
00:50:45.273 --> 00:50:47.642
No.
I won't turn the pistol over.

934
00:50:47.773 --> 00:50:49.608
But she must be punished
for this.

935
00:50:49.666 --> 00:50:50.901
JAMIE: Aye. you're right.

936
00:50:50.959 --> 00:50:52.264
Laoghaire deserves
to be punished.

937
00:50:52.321 --> 00:50:55.493
but... I willna do it
to the girls.

938
00:50:56.330 --> 00:50:58.235
They're already losing a father.

939
00:50:58.341 --> 00:51:01.344
I-I won't have them lose
a mother as well.

940
00:51:06.904 --> 00:51:08.405
What does Laoghaire want?

941
00:51:09.495 --> 00:51:12.329
Well. I believe her chief desire
is to have you castrated

942
00:51:12.387 --> 00:51:15.056
and your bollocks mounted
on her wall.

943
00:51:15.114 --> 00:51:19.919
but I suspect that she may
be amenable to alimony.

944
00:51:21.720 --> 00:51:23.022
How much?

945
00:51:25.800 --> 00:51:27.269
[ quill clinks inkwell ]

946
00:51:28.932 --> 00:51:32.870
20 pounds?
That's two years' wages!

947
00:51:32.931 --> 00:51:35.834
And 10 pounds a year to maintain
a household for the girls

948
00:51:35.910 --> 00:51:37.540
until they're properly wed.

949
00:51:37.710 --> 00:51:39.312
That's an outrageous sum.

950
00:51:39.436 --> 00:51:41.048
[ scoffs ]

951
00:51:41.234 --> 00:51:43.069
Aye. I ken.

952
00:51:43.295 --> 00:51:46.432
But I wo... I won't put
that burden on you.

953
00:51:46.688 --> 00:51:49.391
Where do ye intend
to get the money to pay her?

954
00:51:49.610 --> 00:51:52.228
There's a place I know.

955
00:51:52.824 --> 00:51:56.931
There's a box
full of ancient coins...

956
00:51:57.343 --> 00:51:59.446
on Silkie Island.

957
00:51:59.998 --> 00:52:01.563
I swam there once.

958
00:52:01.843 --> 00:52:03.970
JAMIE: Maybe I could go back
and get it.

959
00:52:04.028 --> 00:52:05.438
CLAIRE: You can't swim anywhere.

960
00:52:05.496 --> 00:52:07.181
not until that arm's healed.

961
00:52:07.375 --> 00:52:09.177
YOUNG IAN: How far is it?

962
00:52:11.344 --> 00:52:13.279
Mebbe a quarter mile.

963
00:52:14.121 --> 00:52:16.056
Aye.
I can swim that.

964
00:52:16.280 --> 00:52:18.040
I'm a better swimmer
than either of my brothers.

965
00:52:18.097 --> 00:52:19.098
JENNY: Away you go.

966
00:52:19.174 --> 00:52:21.009
You can bring that in later.

967
00:52:25.447 --> 00:52:28.116
Well. what good are ancient
coins in the Highlands?

968
00:52:28.174 --> 00:52:30.443
Laoghaire canna use them
for food and rents.

969
00:52:30.650 --> 00:52:32.585
I'll take them to France.

970
00:52:32.685 --> 00:52:36.356
Cousin Jared will know
how to trade them for sterling.

971
00:52:36.456 --> 00:52:38.558
He's family.
He'll be discreet.

972
00:52:38.658 --> 00:52:41.970
Then I'll bring the proceeds
back for Laoghaire.

973
00:52:43.130 --> 00:52:46.978
I'd also like to take
young Ian to France as well.

974
00:52:47.105 --> 00:52:48.273
if that's all right with you.

975
00:52:48.468 --> 00:52:50.196
- [ sighs ]
JAMIE: He's old enough

976
00:52:50.384 --> 00:52:53.306
to see a bit of the world
outside of Scotland.

977
00:52:53.493 --> 00:52:55.446
You and I had our time
in France. Ian.

978
00:52:55.634 --> 00:52:57.577
Better that than war.

979
00:53:03.683 --> 00:53:06.419
I suppose it's best
we let him have his freedom

980
00:53:06.519 --> 00:53:09.871
while he still thinks
it's ours to give.

981
00:53:11.715 --> 00:53:14.809
You'll take better take care
of him this time. aye?

982
00:53:15.348 --> 00:53:16.696
We will.

983
00:53:16.796 --> 00:53:19.632
♪♪ Dramatic music...

984
00:53:19.732 --> 00:53:21.397
♪♪

985
00:53:21.850 --> 00:53:23.214
You can trust us.

986
00:53:23.272 --> 00:53:26.173
♪♪

987
00:53:30.910 --> 00:53:33.513
The water must be freezing.

988
00:53:33.784 --> 00:53:34.839
'Tis.

989
00:53:35.003 --> 00:53:37.217
♪♪

990
00:53:37.815 --> 00:53:40.804
JAMIE: It's the current
that's the worst part of it.

991
00:53:40.862 --> 00:53:43.096
♪♪

992
00:53:43.323 --> 00:53:45.131
Ye must surrender to it.

993
00:53:45.224 --> 00:53:47.085
JAMIE: But as ye come nearer
the island.

994
00:53:47.143 --> 00:53:48.233
ye must break free of it

995
00:53:48.291 --> 00:53:50.563
or be carried away
to the New World.

996
00:53:50.663 --> 00:53:52.326
♪♪

997
00:53:52.469 --> 00:53:53.658
Dinna fash.

998
00:53:53.743 --> 00:53:55.338
Ian's a braw swimmer.

999
00:53:55.432 --> 00:53:58.369
♪♪

1000
00:54:07.647 --> 00:54:10.483
♪♪ Somber music...

1001
00:54:10.583 --> 00:54:11.751
♪♪

1002
00:54:11.851 --> 00:54:13.253
[ spyglass clicks ]

1003
00:54:13.967 --> 00:54:17.107
We've barely been alone
since we left Edinburgh.

1004
00:54:17.271 --> 00:54:20.857
Now we're the only two people
on this cliff.

1005
00:54:21.060 --> 00:54:22.475
and ye canna meet my eye.

1006
00:54:22.865 --> 00:54:25.818
♪♪

1007
00:54:28.231 --> 00:54:30.872
I'm afraid th-this is...

1008
00:54:31.395 --> 00:54:33.302
all a mistake.

1009
00:54:33.497 --> 00:54:36.276
♪♪

1010
00:54:36.879 --> 00:54:39.719
I'm just not sure
if we belong together anymore.

1011
00:54:39.812 --> 00:54:41.091
♪♪

1012
00:54:41.239 --> 00:54:42.667
How can ye say that?

1013
00:54:42.725 --> 00:54:44.662
♪♪

1014
00:54:44.873 --> 00:54:46.717
I had a life.

1015
00:54:47.459 --> 00:54:49.264
We both had lives.

1016
00:54:49.678 --> 00:54:51.170
And families.

1017
00:54:51.396 --> 00:54:53.146
♪

1018
00:54:53.350 --> 00:54:55.607
It wasn't the plan. but...

1019
00:54:55.795 --> 00:54:58.545
I didn't hate Boston.

1020
00:54:59.678 --> 00:55:01.459
I had a career.

1021
00:55:01.631 --> 00:55:03.603
A home.

1022
00:55:04.037 --> 00:55:06.172
Friends.

1023
00:55:06.740 --> 00:55:09.693
And you had your print shop
in Edinburgh.

1024
00:55:11.287 --> 00:55:13.279
It wasn't so bad.
really. was it?

1025
00:55:13.420 --> 00:55:15.287
♪♪

1026
00:55:15.529 --> 00:55:18.740
Being a printer was naught
compared to being your husband.

1027
00:55:18.904 --> 00:55:21.777
♪♪

1028
00:55:27.152 --> 00:55:30.763
For 20 years. I was haunted
by the memory of you.

1029
00:55:30.972 --> 00:55:33.215
♪♪

1030
00:55:33.512 --> 00:55:36.636
The moment I found out
you were alive. I...

1031
00:55:36.736 --> 00:55:39.539
♪♪

1032
00:55:40.238 --> 00:55:42.016
But ever since
I've arrived back.

1033
00:55:42.074 --> 00:55:44.696
it's been... so much harder

1034
00:55:44.754 --> 00:55:46.567
than I could ever have imagined.

1035
00:55:47.023 --> 00:55:48.557
When has it ever been easy?

1036
00:55:48.889 --> 00:55:52.060
♪♪

1037
00:55:55.012 --> 00:55:57.023
But I apologized for it.

1038
00:55:57.621 --> 00:56:00.727
I've done all I can
to make it right.

1039
00:56:01.115 --> 00:56:02.488
Ye belong wi' me.

1040
00:56:02.824 --> 00:56:05.340
♪♪

1041
00:56:06.057 --> 00:56:07.588
We're mated for life. Sassenach.

1042
00:56:07.767 --> 00:56:10.737
♪♪

1043
00:56:11.909 --> 00:56:14.433
Will you risk the man I am

1044
00:56:14.511 --> 00:56:16.652
for the sake
of the one ye once knew?

1045
00:56:17.113 --> 00:56:19.612
♪♪

1046
00:56:21.225 --> 00:56:22.326
Jamie.

1047
00:56:23.831 --> 00:56:25.207
Christ.

1048
00:56:25.269 --> 00:56:28.020
♪♪ Ominous music...

1049
00:56:28.120 --> 00:56:30.022
[ spyglass clicks ]

1050
00:56:30.137 --> 00:56:33.307
♪♪

1051
00:56:46.920 --> 00:56:48.388
Oh. where's Ian?

1052
00:56:49.845 --> 00:56:51.574
JAMIE: There.

1053
00:56:52.692 --> 00:56:54.332
Making his way down.

1054
00:56:54.816 --> 00:56:56.990
♪♪

1055
00:57:02.163 --> 00:57:04.941
JAMIE: Ian! Ian!

1056
00:57:04.999 --> 00:57:06.097
♪♪

1057
00:57:06.162 --> 00:57:07.631
Go back!

1058
00:57:08.116 --> 00:57:10.062
♪♪

1059
00:57:10.162 --> 00:57:12.999
♪♪ Intense music...

1060
00:57:13.099 --> 00:57:16.068
♪♪

1061
00:57:33.920 --> 00:57:36.856
